title: background_dialogue_rojul_noon_1
tags:
---
Rojul: The sun’s right overhead now.
Rojul: Feels like it’s keeping watch.
===

title: background_dialogue_rojul_noon_2
tags:
---
Rojul: Everything slows down at noon.
Rojul: Even the wind’s taking a nap.
===

title: background_dialogue_rojul_noon_3
tags:
---
Rojul: The crickets are quiet now.
Rojul: I think even they’re hiding from the heat.
===

title: background_dialogue_rojul_noon_4
tags:
---
Rojul: I polished my chestplate this morning.
Rojul: Now it’s reflecting the whole sky.
===

title: background_dialogue_rojul_noon_5
tags:
---
Rojul: This is when the grass smells strongest.
Rojul: Sun-baked and full of memories.
===

title: background_dialogue_rojul_noon_6
tags:
---
Rojul: I used to dread the heat.
Rojul: Now I just drink it in.
===

title: background_dialogue_rojul_noon_7
tags:
---
Rojul: If you squint, the horizon shimmers.
Rojul: Like the plain’s trying to become a dream.
===

title: background_dialogue_rojul_noon_8
tags:
---
Rojul: It’s too bright to think heavy thoughts.
Rojul: That’s why I save joy for the afternoons.
===

title: background_dialogue_rojul_noon_9
tags:
---
Rojul: I like how my shadow hides under me at noon.
Rojul: Like it’s sticking close for shade.
===

title: background_dialogue_rojul_noon_10
tags:
---
Rojul: Noon smells like warm dust and good work.
Rojul: Like the world’s halfway through something important.
===

title: background_dialogue_rojul_noon_11
tags:
---
Rojul: I used to call this lunch hour.
Rojul: Now I just call it listening time.
===

title: background_dialogue_rojul_noon_12
tags:
---
Rojul: The bees are out and buzzing.
Rojul: Busy little machines, just like I used to be.
===

title: background_dialogue_rojul_noon_13
tags:
---
Rojul: My servos hum louder when it’s hot.
Rojul: Sounds like they’re singing.
===

title: background_dialogue_rojul_noon_14
tags:
---
Rojul: Noon light makes everything sharper.
Rojul: Even my thoughts get edges.
===

title: background_dialogue_rojul_noon_15
tags:
---
Rojul: Some folks call this the dead hour.
Rojul: But I’ve never seen the plain more alive.
===
